      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It could absolutely be heteroscedasticity, which means the variance of the error terms changes across different levels of your predictors. This changing variance can manifest as heavy tails and non-normality in the residuals when viewed globally. Beyond heteroscedasticity, the clustered nature of your outliers might point to a latent variable or unmodeled non-linearity that is causing the model to break down for those specific observations. You could test for heteroscedasticity using residual plots against your independent variables.",
